snippet.textDisplay:
I came here just to check out the situation with the lost video. I had chance to watch it - and just saying - it wasn't ANYTHING abusive or horrible. And to people who saw it that way; please reconsider if you may have over-reacted.

In fact that Jenna was testing the product and wondering how their doggos would be safe/safer during car drives is awesome and could possibly make other pet owners wonder the same issue - which is good. Isn't it?

She did also put out there that maybe the product wasn't for Peach and Kermit because their body shapes. And they were TESTING the product and figuring out would it work for them and their dogs. AS you should.. and They didn't drive for hours - they did a trip to dog park..

Yes - it looked like dogs weren't 100% comfortable in the sit-up-seats - but c'mon most animal are uncomfortable when but in even a harness for first time. Then they get use to it and it is fine.

I hope Jenna is ok and not feeling bad because some of those comments. Much love to Jenna and Julien all of their doggos and the giraffe! ❤🤗
